# ⚡ Smart Grid Monitoring and Management System

## 📌 Overview
The Smart Grid Monitoring and Management System is an IoT-based solution designed to monitor electrical distribution lines in real time. It helps improve power reliability, detect faults, prevent energy theft, and enable efficient maintenance of the power grid, especially during climate-related disturbances.

---

## 🚀 Features
- Real-time monitoring of voltage and current in distribution lines  
- ESP32-based IoT communication with cloud database  
- Grid-wise data storage with unique location identification  
- Detection of abnormal conditions and power tampering  
- Climate-condition-based fault prevention support  
- Historical data comparison (current vs previous year ~70% analysis)  
- Easy identification of faulty grid sections  
- Smart maintenance support for field workers  

---

## 🛠️ Components Used
- ESP32 Microcontroller  
- Voltage Sensor  
- Current Sensor  
- Resistor-based measurement circuit  
- Cloud Database (Firebase / MySQL / etc.)  
- Wi-Fi communication module (built-in ESP32)  

---

## ⚙️ Working Principle

The system measures electrical parameters from distribution lines using voltage and current sensors along with resistor-based measurement techniques. The ESP32 microcontroller processes these signals and sends the data to a cloud database in real time.

Each grid/pole is assigned a unique ID and location, allowing easy tracking and monitoring. The system compares current data with historical records to detect anomalies, theft, or faults and helps in efficient maintenance planning.

